Welche flache CSS-Struktur entspricht dem verschachtelten LESS-Code fachlich am ehesten?<br><div class="code-card" style="max-width:900px;border-radius:16px;overflow:hidden;background:#102d42;box-shadow:0 10px 24px rgba(0,0,0,.16);font-family:Consolas,'Courier New',monospace;margin:12px 0;"><div style="height:42px;background:#12334a;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.14);display:flex;align-items:center;padding:0 16px;color:#fff;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-weight:700;"><span style="width:11px;height:11px;background:#ff5f57;border-radius:50%;display:inline-block;margin-right:7px;"></span><span style="width:11px;height:11px;background:#ffbd2e;border-radius:50%;display:inline-block;margin-right:7px;"></span><span style="width:11px;height:11px;background:#28c840;border-radius:50%;display:inline-block;margin-right:13px;"></span>style.less</div><pre style="margin:0;padding:18px 20px;color:#f8fbff;line-height:1.48;font-size:15px;white-space:pre-wrap;background:#102d42;">.card {
  .title { color: @primary; }
}</pre></div>

Welche Aussage passt zum Refactoring?<br><div class="code-card" style="max-width:900px;border-radius:16px;overflow:hidden;background:#102d42;box-shadow:0 10px 24px rgba(0,0,0,.16);font-family:Consolas,'Courier New',monospace;margin:12px 0;"><div style="height:42px;background:#12334a;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.14);display:flex;align-items:center;padding:0 16px;color:#fff;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-weight:700;"><span style="width:11px;height:11px;background:#ff5f57;border-radius:50%;display:inline-block;margin-right:7px;"></span><span style="width:11px;height:11px;background:#ffbd2e;border-radius:50%;display:inline-block;margin-right:7px;"></span><span style="width:11px;height:11px;background:#28c840;border-radius:50%;display:inline-block;margin-right:13px;"></span>style.css</div><pre style="margin:0;padding:18px 20px;color:#f8fbff;line-height:1.48;font-size:15px;white-space:pre-wrap;background:#102d42;">.box { color: #003964; }
.card { color: #003964; }
.hero { color: #003964; }</pre></div>

Welche Aussage passt zur Regel?<br><div class="code-card" style="max-width:900px;border-radius:16px;overflow:hidden;background:#102d42;box-shadow:0 10px 24px rgba(0,0,0,.16);font-family:Consolas,'Courier New',monospace;margin:12px 0;"><div style="height:42px;background:#12334a;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.14);display:flex;align-items:center;padding:0 16px;color:#fff;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-weight:700;"><span style="width:11px;height:11px;background:#ff5f57;border-radius:50%;display:inline-block;margin-right:7px;"></span><span style="width:11px;height:11px;background:#ffbd2e;border-radius:50%;display:inline-block;margin-right:7px;"></span><span style="width:11px;height:11px;background:#28c840;border-radius:50%;display:inline-block;margin-right:13px;"></span>style.css</div><pre style="margin:0;padding:18px 20px;color:#f8fbff;line-height:1.48;font-size:15px;white-space:pre-wrap;background:#102d42;">@font-face {
  font-family: &quot;TrainingSans&quot;;
  src: url(&quot;../fonts/training-sans-bold.woff2&quot;) format(&quot;woff2&quot;);
  font-weight: 700;
  font-display: swap;
}</pre></div>
